{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_start","contentIndex":1,"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my review of the arbitration record and admitted evidence, I have analyzed the proposition: \"Samantha materially misrepresented when the essay would be complete, and that the claimant reasonably relied on that representation.\"\n\nThe key evidence shows:\n1. Samantha gave specific deadline assurances on March 10 and March 11 that the package would be complete for the press window\n2. Peter explicitly conditioned keeping the rush print slot on this deadline\n3. Samantha's assurances were coupled with false claims about having read the required Stephenson essay\n4. The confession proves Samantha had not done the foundational reading work she claimed\n5. Peter relied on these assurances to approve an $85,000 printing invoice and $15,000 distribution work order\n\nWhile the defense correctly notes there's no direct evidence proving the package was actually late, the material misrepresentation occurred at the moment Samantha gave her assurances while concealing her lack of preparation. A retained writer who falsely claims to have done required foundational work materially misrepresents completion timing when giving deadline assurances that control significant commercial decisions.\n\nPeter's reliance was reasonable - he asked twice, made the consequences clear, and relied on the person with superior knowledge of the work status. The preponderance of evidence supports that Samantha's timing assurances were materially misleading."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2b2f","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"Samantha materially misrepresented completion timing by giving deadline assurances while falsely claiming she had done the required foundational reading work. Peter reasonably relied on these assurances to approve significant commercial printing commitments after making the consequences clear.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"Samantha materially misrepresented completion timing by giving deadline assurances while falsely claiming she had done the required foundational reading work. Peter reasonably relied on these assurances to approve significant commercial printing commitments after making the consequences clear.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782753353551,"responseId":"gen-1782753353-xskkkRSDXWnzfnvXDGHv"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my review of the arbitration record and admitted evidence, I have analyzed the proposition: \"Samantha materially misrepresented when the essay would be complete, and that the claimant reasonably relied on that representation.\"\n\nThe key evidence shows:\n1. Samantha gave specific deadline assurances on March 10 and March 11 that the package would be complete for the press window\n2. Peter explicitly conditioned keeping the rush print slot on this deadline\n3. Samantha's assurances were coupled with false claims about having read the required Stephenson essay\n4. The confession proves Samantha had not done the foundational reading work she claimed\n5. Peter relied on these assurances to approve an $85,000 printing invoice and $15,000 distribution work order\n\nWhile the defense correctly notes there's no direct evidence proving the package was actually late, the material misrepresentation occurred at the moment Samantha gave her assurances while concealing her lack of preparation. A retained writer who falsely claims to have done required foundational work materially misrepresents completion timing when giving deadline assurances that control significant commercial decisions.\n\nPeter's reliance was reasonable - he asked twice, made the consequences clear, and relied on the person with superior knowledge of the work status. The preponderance of evidence supports that Samantha's timing assurances were materially misleading."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2b2f","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"Samantha materially misrepresented completion timing by giving deadline assurances while falsely claiming she had done the required foundational reading work. Peter reasonably relied on these assurances to approve significant commercial printing commitments after making the consequences clear.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"Samantha materially misrepresented completion timing by giving deadline assurances while falsely claiming she had done the required foundational reading work. Peter reasonably relied on these assurances to approve significant commercial printing commitments after making the consequences clear.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"deepseek/deepseek-v3.1-terminus","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782753353551,"responseId":"gen-1782753353-xskkkRSDXWnzfnvXDGHv"}}
